        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="516" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <head>No. 512.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hitt</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">de
                                    Zamacona</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-08-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 16,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Adverting to your complaint of the 25th of
                            July last, relative to the crossing into Mexico of a sheriff and party,
                            and the capturing of a fugitive criminal who was brought back into this
                            country, I have now the honor to inform you that the Acting Secretary of
                            the Interior has advised this Department, under date of the 9th instant,
                            that the governor of Arizona Territory had been instructed to
                            investigate the subject, and to take all proper measures for the
                            punishment of any guilty persons, and for preservation of peace along
                            the frontier.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R. R. HITT,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
